# FE form layout (dialogs, sheets, settings)

Apply these rules to create/edit forms in modals, sheets, and admin pages.

## Grid rules

- **Mobile first:** single column on default; multi-column from `sm:` or `md:` only.
- **Prefer 2 columns** on desktop for paired fields (name + email, role + status, city + state).
- **Do not use 3 columns** unless the form has 6+ short fields that fill rows evenly. Avoid orphan columns (e.g. row 1 has 3 fields, row 2 has 2).
- **Full-width rows** for: password, textarea, rich text, file upload, permission pickers, long selects.
- **Equal column width:** use `grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2` — never mix 3-col and 2-col rows in the same form without `col-span-full`.

## Section grouping

Group related fields with visual sections (common admin pattern):

```tsx
<div className="space-y-6">
  <fieldset className="space-y-4">
    <legend className="text-sm font-medium">Section title</legend>
    <div className="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">{/* paired fields */}</div>
    {/* full-width field if needed */}
  </fieldset>
</div>
```

- **Identity / account:** name, email, password
- **Access / permissions:** role, status, permission keys
- **Metadata:** slug, description (when applicable)

## Labels and hints

- Every input needs a visible `<Label>` — never placeholder-only.
- Put optional/long hints in **helper text** below the label (`text-xs text-muted-foreground`), not appended to the label string.
- Keep labels short; move “leave blank to keep current” to helper text.

## Dialog / sheet width

| Layout | Tailwind max-width |
|--------|-------------------|
| 1 column (≤4 simple fields) | `sm:max-w-md` or `sm:max-w-lg` |
| 2 columns (typical CRUD) | `sm:max-w-xl` or `sm:max-w-2xl` |
| Wide pickers / tables inside | `sm:max-w-2xl lg:max-w-3xl` |

Match width to column count — do not use `max-w-3xl` for a 2-field form.

## Footer

- Sticky footer with `border-t bg-muted/30` for scrollable body.
- Actions right-aligned on `sm+`: Cancel (outline) + primary submit.
- Full-width stacked buttons on mobile only.

## Reference patterns

- shadcn [Field](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/field) — label + control + description + error
- Pair related inputs horizontally; stack unrelated or sensitive fields vertically
- One primary action per form footer
